headline: PNC Multifamily Capital Announces $208 Million Affordable Housing Fund, Increasing Access to Affordable Housing Across the U.S.
summary: PNC Bank, N.A., a tax credit syndication leader, today announced the closing of Low-Income Housing Tax Credit (LIHTC) Fund 98, which is investing more than $208 million in the development and rehabilitation of affordable rental housing across the U.S. The fund includes investments from PNC and seven other financial services and insurance companies, including two investors that are new to PNC's LIHTC funds.

headline: US Financial 15 Split Corp. Preferred Dividend Declared
summary: TORONTO, June 18, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- US Financial 15 Split Corp ("US Financial 15") declares its monthly distribution of $0.06167 for each Preferred share, or 10.00% annually based on the previous month end net asset value. Distributions are payable July 10, 2025 to shareholders on record as at June 30, 2025. US Financial 15 invests in a portfolio consisting of 15 U.S. financial services companies as follows: American Express, Bank of America, Bank of New York Mellon Corp., Citigroup, CME
